The paper deals with the task of temporally grounding language queries in videos, which involves both visual and linguistic understanding. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The proposed model also involves boundary prediction and contextual modeling, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper uses an end-to-end approach, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
